dan-glasses-daemons for Debian
-----------------------------

This package installs six HTTP daemons that form the runtime backbone of
the Dan Glasses wearable AI assistant:

  * dan-glasses-audiod        :8090  VAD (Silero) + STT (whisper.cpp)
  * dan-glasses-perceptiond   :8092  Camera capture + VLM (LFM2.5-VL-450M)
  * dan-glasses-memoryd       :8741  SQLite + sentence-transformers
  * dan-glasses-toold         :8742  Sandboxed shell / python execution
  * dan-glasses-ttsd          :8743  KittenTTS + gTTS + espeak-ng
  * dan-glasses-os-toold      :8744  Path-guarded OS tool surface

All units are enabled on install but NOT started automatically; bring them
up with `systemctl start dan-glasses-<name>` once you have a microphone /
camera plugged in.

Persistent state lives in /var/lib/dan-glasses and is preserved across
upgrades. Logs go through journald (`journalctl -u dan-glasses-audiod -f`).

The OpenClaw gateway is configured separately, typically in
/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json, and is not part of this package.

